    "name": "Clockwork Excavator",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "The product of greed and invention, clockwork excavators are designed to strip-mine an area in pursuit of mineral wealth. Found in areas where such desires override any concern for the natural environment, clockwork excavators are durable, tough, and purpose-driven."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Set atop spoked wheels, this huge contraption has two hinged arms that appear to be designed to shovel rocks into its open maw. Gleaming drills set around the construct\u2019s base look like they could easily break apart stone, and a gleaming scope of dark-hued glass projects from the end of a jointed arm.</i>",
